Brother charged after Aberdare woman found dead The brother of a woman from Aberdare found dead in Cumbria on Saturday has been charged with her murder . 23 - year - old John Jenkin , of Millom , has been charged with the murder of his 58 - year - old mother , Alice McMeekin , and sister , Kathryn Jenkin , 20 , who is from Aberdare . On Saturday 8 June 2013 , at 8 : 39am police were called to a property in Newton Street where Mrs McMeekin and Miss Jenkin were tragically found dead with head injuries . The family dog was also found dead . John Jenkin was arrested on suspicion of murder shortly afterwards . He will appear at Furness District Magistrates court this morning . John Jenkin is related to the victims , he is the son of Alice McMeekin and the brother of Kathryn Jenkin . - CUMBRIA POLICE
